<br>
Bards - Don't stay 52 waiting for a white scale.  You can't complete epic until you are capable of killing Trak.  If you are in a guild that can kill Trak, you can probably kill Gore, and get your white scale there.  My advice to you is to forget epic for now and just LEVEL.<br>
<br>
Warriors - Don't stay 52 waiting for a red scale.  You can buy them in EC for under 10k.  Even if you don't have the PP, the red scale is one of the easier parts of the warrior epic.  You need a guild effort to get Green Scale, Queen blade, Spiroc blade.  Not many pick-up raids can get these.  You might get lucky and get Hate/Fear parts on pick up raid, but you still won't be able to complete your epic until you get into a guild that can kill the tougher mobs.  My advice to you is to forget epic for now and just LEVEL.<br>
<br>
Pallies - Don't stay 52 waiting for pally books.  Go on Vox/Naggy raids from 50-52.  If you get lucky and get your books, then good for you.  If you don't, then it really isn't that big of deal.   There are many quality 1hs/2hs that are for pally/SK's only, as well as the ones that are open to all tanks.   Either way, pallies aren't desidered for the damage they do, they are desired for the spells they can use.  The higher their level, the better their spells.  My advice to you is to forget epic for now and just LEVEL.<br>
<br>
Now let's look at the quality of these three epics -<br>
<br>
Bards - Class defining.  I don't think they will ever put them down.<br>
<br>
Warriors - At the higher end game you will end up putting your epic in backpack.  <br>
<br>
Pallidans - At the higher end game you will end up putting your epic in backpack.<br>
<br>
So, with all of that said:<br>
<br>
Bards - Go on Vox/Naggy raids until 52, then focus on Leveling.  Once you get up their in levels, get into a guild that can take Trak, then worry about epic again.  Levels are the most important thing in game.<br>
<br>
Warriors/Pallies -  If the epic falls into your lap, then take it.  But given a choice between leveling and working on epic, I would recommend leveling.  A 60 warrior/pally without epic is WAAAAAY more valuable to a raid than a 55 warrior/pally with epic.<br>
