 <br>
<br>
There are weapons that do more damage, but the stun proc and the fact that a pally can bash with this weapon make it extremely useful (not to mention the +15WIS and +30 MANA that aid greatly with a Pally's spells).  Will I put this in my backpack someday? - won't consider it until I get the AA ability to 2H bash with  any weapon - and that won't be for awhile after I am 60 -  and then it would have to be for a weapon that also had the mana and wisdom...  such as:<br>
<br>
NORGE'TAL <br>
Statistical Information<br>
Classes:  Paladins, Shadow Knights<br>
Races:  All Races<br>
Type: 2H Slash<br>
Damage: 53<br>
Delay: 45<br>
Stats:  +100 MANA +100 HP +5 AGI +10 INT +5 STA +10 WIS<br>
Special Attributes:  MAGIC, NO DROP, LORE<br>
Slot(s):  Primary<br>
Weight:  1 Stone<br>
Rec Level:  51<br>
Effect:  Descending Might   <br>
Acquistion Information<br>
Dropped by:  Coming soon!<br>
Zone: Ssraeshzra Temple<br>
 <br>
Pricing Information<br>
Average cost: Item Not Tradeable<br>
 <br>
Miscellaneous Information<br>
Rarity: Common<br>
Proc Level:  Unknown<br>
Max Damage: 299.45<br>
Damage/Delay Ratio: Godly (1.177)<br>
Max Attack Speed: A Bit Slow (25)<br>
Weapon Performance: Phenomenal (17.766)<br>
Effect Details:  -unknown- <br>
<br>
But then to get that, have to be in an uber guild to get it - fine and dandy if you have the time to participate in those guilds - anyway enough of my ranting.  The Fiery Defender is a respectable weapon and worth getting for those pallys that cannot use Nature's Defender.  I put exp into AA at 52 to make sure I got my books first - didn't hold me back that long, but then again, maybe I got lucky - attended 1 naggy and 16 vox raids to get both books ---<br>
<br>
